topic.title: Problem Status - conformance rules

section.p:
The Problem Status records whether the indicated problem is active, inactive, or resolved.
THIS TEMPLATE HAS BEEN DEPRECATED IN C-CDA R2 AND MAY BE DELETED FROM A FUTURE RELEASE OF THIS IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE. USE OF THIS TEMPLATE IS NOT RECOMMENDED.
Reason for deprecation: Per the explanation in Volume 1, Section 3.2 "Determining a Clinical Statement's Status", the status of a problem is determined based on attributes of the Problem Observation

ol.li:
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] templateId ( CONF:7359 ) such that it
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @root="2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.22.4.6"
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="OBS" Observation (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:7357)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:7358)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] code/@code="33999-4" Status (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.6.1 LOINC) (CONF:7361)
SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] text (CONF:7362)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] statusCode/@code="completed" Completed (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.14 ActStatus) (CONF:7364)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] value with @xsi:type="CD", which SHALL be selected from ValueSet HITSP Problem Status 2.16.840.1.113883.3.88.12.80.68 STATIC (CONF:7365)
text, if present, SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] reference (CONF:15593)
reference, if present, SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @value (CONF:15594)
reference/@value SHALL begin with a '#' and SHALL point to its corresponding narrative (using the approach defined in CDA Release 2, section 4.3.5.1) (CONF:15595)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="OBS" Observation (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:7357)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:7358)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] code/@code="33999-4" Status (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.6.1 LOINC) (CONF:7361)
SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] text (CONF:7362)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] statusCode/@code="completed" Completed (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.14 ActStatus) (CONF:7364)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] value with @xsi:type="CD", which SHALL be selected from ValueSet HITSP Problem Status 2.16.840.1.113883.3.88.12.80.68 STATIC (CONF:7365)
text, if present, SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] reference (CONF:15593)
reference, if present, SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @value (CONF:15594)
reference/@value SHALL begin with a '#' and SHALL point to its corresponding narrative (using the approach defined in CDA Release 2, section 4.3.5.1) (CONF:15595)
